{
  "texts": [
    "This is exemplified in online movements, where personalized content sharing allows for greater flexibility in adapting frames to mobilize diverse audiences, as opposed to relying on singular rigid collective action frames (Bennett and Segerberg, 2011, 2012).",
    "On Twitter, posts are public by default and visible to one's full list of followers and beyond.",
    "However, people have diverse strategies to navigate this \"context collapse\" to reach intended sub-audiences (Marwick and boyd, 2011), such as through addressivity markers (Meraz and Papacharissi, 2013).",
    "Twitter's interactional features offer another mechanism for targeting intended audiences; different types of tweets (original \"broadcast\" tweets, quote tweets, and replies) have different intended audiences and communicative goals (Garimella et al., 2016).",
    "Issue Areas."
  ]
}